bio.experienceSummary: I am a 39-year-old mother of one wonderful 14-year-old girl now a 9th grader and she is the love of my life! I have over 13+ years of experience as a nanny. I can provide excellent verifiable reference available. I am seeking work ideally in Brooklyn and Staten Island, Manhattan. I am a hands on individual who enjoys arts and crafts, singing, reading and above all playing with children. I take care of all the light housekeeping duties pertaining to the children as well. I can run any errands you might need done, groceries, laundry and clean up the nursery/room. I have several reliable transportation options. Most importantly I will treat and care for your children as if they were my own. Their safety and well being is of utmost importance to me. CPR and first aide certified. I enjoy the outdoors and recreation.

description.originalText: We had a trial run with Erika and she was excellent. The moment she stepped in, she was professional and definitely showed a high standard of care.

bio.experienceSummary:
Hello, I'm a former teacher and mom of 4 children who are now ages 19-25. I'm Math teacher by education and training. I speak both English and Russian. 
I'm mature, caring, patient, attentive, engaging, experienced in infant/ child care and education. I'm reliable and punctual. I've been assisting families with infants and young children in Bayonne, Jersey City, Hoboken, Weehawken, NYC. I love to read to the children, engage them in fun and educational activities. I will create safe environment for your child. I also enjoy taking kids to the park/ playground ( weather/ CDC guidelines permit).
I'm up to date with Flu, Pneumonia, TDaP vaccinations.
I'm fully vaccinated and boosted.
By all means I welcome background check.

description.originalText:
Whatever I write here will not do Svetlana justice. She was flexible and endlessly kind and she helped us make our weekend trip a resounding success. She walked in and my nephew was almost immediately at ease. He had such a good time with Svetlana singing and drawing together. She certainly left an impression as he was asking about her after we'd left town. 

Anyway, I can't really say enough good things. Thank you Svetlana for taking care of our little guy.

bio.experienceSummary: My name is Marina, I'm a collage student studying early childhood education. I would say I'm a very calm and patient person. Im also very caring when it comes to a child's need. I grew up taking care of my baby cousins while their parents are at work and whenever they needed assistance in the house. I have worked with ages 4 months- 4 years old. I'm great with kids and kind. I don't raise my voice or yell I'm very understanding when a kid is upset and do my best to calm them down and cheer them up when upset. I have been babysitting for 3 years now on the app and met a lot of great families.

description.originalText: Marina was great. Kids enjoyed playing with her. Would definitely recommend and use her again.

bio.experienceSummary:
I'm passionate about fostering the growth and development of children. With over four years of experience, I'm skilled at caring for kids of all ages, from infants to preteens. My patient and calm demeanor, coupled with my creativity and imagination, allows me to connect with children and make learning fun.

I believe in open communication with parents and regularly provide written daily reports and updates via text or phone call, whichever you prefer. I prioritize following your lead when it comes to enforcing household rules and am comfortable caring for up to two children at a time.

From outdoor sports to educational games and technology-based apps, I love engaging children in a variety of activities that promote physical, mental, and emotional development. My experience includes caring for my brother since he was a baby and I have a2-year-old son of my own. I'm excited to bring my passion and expertise to your family!

description.originalText: Arianna is an amazing individual. She was very patient with my daughter. Her communication skills were excellent, I felt more than safe leaving my little girl with her!

bio.experienceSummary:
I've been a childcare provider for over seven years. I'm passionate about helping children grow and develop. I'm patient, calm, creative, and friendly. I believe in open communication with parents and follow their preferred communication method to discuss their child's day or any issues.

My goal is to provide a safe and nurturing environment where children can learn, play, and grow. I'm comfortable enforcing household rules as directed by the parents. I love playing outdoor games, educational games, and technology-based games and apps with children.

I have a bachelor's degree and am fluent in Arabic, English, French, and Spanish. I have CPR and First Aid training. I have a car and am comfortable with pets.

I'm excited about the opportunity to care for your child and help them reach their full potential.

I'm a Responsible childcare professional experienced in guiding children and documenting learning and development. Background leading fun activities to teach new skills and encourage growth.
I consider myself as a patient and responsible person , very open and communicative !
I have experience with children between infants to 12 years old . I was nanny for different families in the city. Also I was teacher for 2-3years old .

description.displayText: Shqiponja was so sweet and so great with my daughter. My daughter loved her and she was so professional. I would definitely hire her again!
description.originalText: Shqiponja was so sweet and so great with my daughter. My daughter loved her and she was so professional. I would definitely hire her again!

bio.experienceSummary: Hi there! My name is Madeline, I am 26 years old and am currently a full-time student during the day and have been working with children ranging from 6 months through 12 years old, as well as adults with physical disabilities. I have a background in healthcare and am CPR certified, I am available during the week any time after 5 p.m.  with occasional earlier availability depending on my class schedule. I love board games, cooking, and gardening!

Hello! I'm Nicole and I'm a professional child care provider. I'm first aid, CPR and EMT certified. I have years of experience caring for newborns, toddlers and primary school children. I'm available for full-time, live out, occasional, and part-time nanny roles.

I'm passionate about providing a safe and nurturing environment that helps children reach their full potential. I'm highly experienced with routine creation and planning age appropriate activities that will engage and stimulate the children. 

If you're looking for a professional child care provider for your newborn, toddler, or primary school child, I'd love to hear from you. Please feel free to message me if you're interested!

Hello, I'm Desiree, and I am excited to offer my childcare services. With over 10 years of experience working with children, I am confident in my ability to provide a nurturing and fun environment for kids. For the past 9 years, I have been a full-time educator. In addition, I've had the pleasure of working as a private tutor and a babysitter. I've worked with children ranging from 4 months to 14 years old, helping to support their growth, development, and learning at every stage. 

As I seek a full-time childcare position, I'm looking forward to bringing my experience, attention to detail, and dedication to a family where I can create a safe and engaging environment. 

If you're looking for a reliable, responsible, and experienced caregiver, I'd love to connect and discuss how I can support your family's needs!

A skilled and kind nanny who genuinely loves working with kids and wants to give a family the best care possible. With 7 years of childcare expertise, a caring demeanor, effective communication abilities, and a commitment to creating a secure and stimulating place for kids to flourish. I also have experience working as a Neonatal Intensive Care PCA, so much experience with newborns and preemies!
*resume can be sent anytime*

description.originalText:
I always say that I’m so thankful to have family that lives close because I have quick access to childcare, but sometimes your family’s schedule gets busy too!

As a new mom, I was hesitant leaving my babygirl (and our puppy!) with someone new BUT Michaela eased all of my anxiety. She’s so gentle, nurturing and patient—you can tell she truly cares.

Her peaceful spirit is infectious and she’s so prompt when responding to my check in messages.

Michaela is a gem and our family is so grateful to have come across her!

Warmly, 
Kiara
